%N A394170 Decimal expansion of the mean volume of a tetrahedron whose vertices are uniformly and independently selected at random in the interior of a regular octahedron of unit volume.
%C A394170 The problem of calculating this constant was mentioned by Zinani (2003). It was evaluated by Weisstein as 0.01368, and calculated by Beck (2022).
%H A394170 Dominik Beck, <a href="https://kdm.karlin.mff.cuni.cz/m8/doktorandska-odpoledne/2022-beck.pdf">Octahedron tetrahedron picking: Expected volume of a random tetrahedron in a regular octahedron</a>, 2022.
%H A394170 Dominik Beck, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.07952">On Random Simplex Picking Beyond the Blashke Problem</a>, arXiv:2412.07952 [math.MG], 2024.
%H A394170 Dominik Beck, <a href="https://www2.karlin.mff.cuni.cz/~beckd/lectures/DISSERTATION.pdf">Random polytopes</a>, doctoral thesis, Mathematical Institute of Charles University, Prague, 2025.
%H A394170 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/OctahedronTetrahedronPicking.html">Octahedron Tetrahedron Picking</a>.
%H A394170 Alessandro Zinani, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00605-002-0531-y">The expected volume of a tetrahedron whose vertices are chosen at random in the interior of a cube</a>, Monatshefte für Mathematik, Vol. 139, No. 4 (2003), pp. 341-348.
%H A394170 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A394170 Equals 19297*Pi^2/3843840 - 6619/184320.
%e A394170 0.0136374112765241754602123153299677982932384778749528...
%t A394170 RealDigits[19297*Pi^2/3843840 - 6619/184320, 10, 120, -1][[1]]
%o A394170 (PARI) 19297*Pi^2/3843840 - 6619/184320
%Y A394170 Tetrahedron volume in: A093524 (cube), A093525 (tetrahedron), A093591 (ball), A394169 (surface of sphere), this constant (octahedron), A394171 (rhombic dodecahedron), A394172 (cuboctahedron), A394173 (truncated tetrahedron), A394174 (triangular bipyramid), A394175 (triangular prism), A394176 (square pyramid).
%K A394170 nonn,cons,new
%O A394170 0,3
